  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Also, beginning at 5th level, when you would cast a Bukijutsu that would start or increase your chain, you gain the following benefits: Chain Start: Until the end of the current Chain, you can gain one of the following effects:</p><hr /><p><strong>Chain Start</strong>: Until the end of the current Chain, you can gain one of the following effects: </p><ul><li><p>Offensive Chain: all Bukijutsu you cast add 1 Flurry die to its damage. This can occur a number of times per casting equal to its Chain value. </p></li><li><p>Defensive Chain: When you would cast a Bukijutsu with the Chain keyword, you roll 1 flurry die and gain the amount as Temporary hit points. </p></li></ul><p><strong>Chain 2:</strong> When you would cast a Chain 2 for the first time in a chain, you can roll 1 flurry die. You can either increase the attack roll by the amount rolled, or the save DC by half the amount rolled. </p><p><strong>Chain 3:</strong> When you damage a creature with a Chain jutsu, you gain an amount of temporary health equal to 1 flurry die.</p>",
